            <article class="layout-article" id="firehose-40033367">
        <header class="story-header">
            
            <h1 id="title-40033367"><a href="//beta.slashdot.org/story/12/11/16/0434236/wordpress-to-accept-bitcoins">WordPress To Accept Bitcoins</a></h1>
            
                <h4>
                    
                    <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/~samzenpus" class="author">samzenpus</a> posted  about a year and a half ago  | from the what-about-gold? dept. 
                    

                    
                </h4>
            
                <span class="topic" id="topic-40033367"> <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/index2.pl?fhfilter=bitcoin" onclick="return addfhfilter('bitcoin');">
            <img src="//c.fsdn.com/s/topics/bitcoin_64.png" width="30px" height="30px" alt="Bitcoin" title="Bitcoin">
        </a></span>
                <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/story/12/11/16/0434236/wordpress-to-accept-bitcoins"><span class="comment-count">205</span></a>
        </header>
	
            
        <div class="elips" data-link="//beta.slashdot.org/story/12/11/16/0434236/wordpress-to-accept-bitcoins">
            <p  id="text-40033367">
                    
                        <a href="http://techworld.com.au/" rel="nofollow">angry tapir</a> writes <i>"WordPress has said it will <a href="http://www.computerworld.com.au/article/442274/wordpress_accept_bitcoins_due_paypal_credit_card_blocks/">accept payment in bitcoins</a>, opening up the blogging platform to payments from users in countries not supported by PayPal or credit card companies. WordPress is free, open-source software, but the company Automattic offers paid-for features such as blog designs, custom domains, hosting partnerships and anti-spam measures."</i>
                        
                    
            </p>
        </div>
        <footer class="article-footer">
            
        </footer>
	
